{
  "info": {
    "name": "Workflow Builder API",
    "description": "HTTP API for the workflow-builder service (Express + MongoDB + BullMQ).\n\n---\n**Collection variables**\n- `baseUrl` — e.g. `http://localhost:3000`\n- `accessToken` — JWT string (set **Authorization** via the **Headers** tab on each protected request; value is `{{accessToken}}`. The API accepts a raw JWT or `Bearer <jwt>` in that header — this collection uses the **header** only, not Postman’s *Bearer Token* auth type.)\n- `workflowId` — set to a real workflow `_id` from **List workflows** or **Create** response\n\n---\n**Auth**\n- **POST /auth/register** — body: `name`, `email`, `password` (min 8 chars). Returns `user` and `token`.\n- **POST /auth/login** — body: `email`, `password`. Returns `user` and `token`.\n- **Register** and **Login** include a **Tests** script that copies `token` into the collection variable `accessToken` when present.\n\n---\n**Prerequisites**\n- **MongoDB** (`MONGODB_URI` in `.env`)\n- **Redis** at `REDIS_HOST` / `REDIS_PORT` (defaults `127.0.0.1:6379`). Webhooks **enqueue** jobs; the **worker** processes them. Redis must be up or enqueue fails.\n\n---\n**Execution rules**\n- Only **`published`** workflows are executed.\n- **Graph:** there must be a **start node** (a node that is never the `to` of any edge). Samples use one node and `edges: []`.\n- **Run** documents store **`jobId`**: BullMQ job id when run via **worker** (webhook path); **UUID** when the scheduler calls `executeWorkflow` directly (no queue).\n\n---\n**Webhook**\n- **POST /webhook/:id** enqueues work and returns **202** with `{ \"message\", \"jobId\" }` (BullMQ id). Execution is asynchronous; check **`runs`** in MongoDB or server logs.\n- Send **`x-webhook-secret`** only when `trigger.config.secret` is set (must match).",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "baseUrl",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000"
    },
    {
      "key": "accessToken",
      "value": "PASTE_JWT_HERE"
    },
    {
      "key": "workflowId",
      "value": "REPLACE_WITH_MONGODB_OBJECTID"
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Health",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Root — API running",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Register",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "try {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (j.token) pm.collectionVariables.set(\"accessToken\", j.token);",
                  "} catch (e) {}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Test User\",\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/register",
            "description": "Creates a user and returns JWT in `token`. Tests script stores it in `accessToken`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "try {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (j.token) pm.collectionVariables.set(\"accessToken\", j.token);",
                  "} catch (e) {}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"test@example.com\",\n  \"password\": \"password123\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/auth/login",
            "description": "Returns JWT in `token`. Tests script stores it in `accessToken`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "User",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get profile",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "{{accessToken}}",
                "description": "Raw JWT or `Bearer <jwt>` — sent as a normal header (not Postman Bearer Token auth)."
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/user/profile",
            "description": "Returns the authenticated user (password omitted). Requires valid JWT."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update profile (partial)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "{{accessToken}}",
                "description": "Raw JWT or `Bearer <jwt>` — sent as a normal header (not Postman Bearer Token auth)."
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Updated name\",\n  \"email\": \"you@example.com\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/user/profile",
            "description": "Send at least one of `name`, `email`."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Workflows",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create workflow",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "try {",
                  "  const j = pm.response.json();",
                  "  const id = j._id || j.id;",
                  "  if (id) pm.collectionVariables.set(\"workflowId\", id);",
                  "} catch (e) {}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "{{accessToken}}",
                "description": "Raw JWT or `Bearer <jwt>` — sent as a normal header (not Postman Bearer Token auth)."
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Sample workflow\",\n  \"status\": \"published\",\n  \"trigger\": {\n    \"type\": \"webhook\",\n    \"config\": {\n      \"secret\": \"optional-shared-secret\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"nodes\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"1\",\n      \"type\": \"http\",\n      \"config\": {\n        \"method\": \"GET\",\n        \"url\": \"https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos/1\"\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"edges\": []\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/workflow",
            "description": "Creates a workflow. Tests script saves returned `_id` into collection variable `workflowId`."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "List workflows",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "{{accessToken}}",
                "description": "Raw JWT or `Bearer <jwt>` — sent as a normal header (not Postman Bearer Token auth)."
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/workflow"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get workflow by id",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "{{accessToken}}",
                "description": "Raw JWT or `Bearer <jwt>` — sent as a normal header (not Postman Bearer Token auth)."
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/workflow/{{workflowId}}"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Update workflow (partial)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PATCH",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "{{accessToken}}",
                "description": "Raw JWT or `Bearer <jwt>` — sent as a normal header (not Postman Bearer Token auth)."
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"status\": \"published\",\n  \"name\": \"Renamed workflow\"\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/workflow/{{workflowId}}"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Replace workflow (full)",
          "request": {
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "{{accessToken}}",
                "description": "Raw JWT or `Bearer <jwt>` — sent as a normal header (not Postman Bearer Token auth)."
              },
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Full replace example\",\n  \"status\": \"published\",\n  \"trigger\": {\n    \"type\": \"cron\",\n    \"config\": {\n      \"cron\": \"0 * * * *\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"nodes\": [\n    {\n      \"id\": \"1\",\n      \"type\": \"http\",\n      \"config\": {\n        \"method\": \"GET\",\n        \"url\": \"https://jsonplaceholder.typicode.com/todos/1\"\n      }\n    }\n  ],\n  \"edges\": []\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/workflow/{{workflowId}}",
            "description": "Replaces the whole document; keep `published` if you need webhook/cron execution to succeed."
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete workflow",
          "request": {
            "method": "DELETE",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Authorization",
                "value": "{{accessToken}}",
                "description": "Raw JWT or `Bearer <jwt>` — sent as a normal header (not Postman Bearer Token auth)."
              }
            ],
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/workflow/{{workflowId}}"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Triggers",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Webhook — trigger workflow",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              },
              {
                "key": "x-webhook-secret",
                "value": "optional-shared-secret",
                "description": "Omit this header if the workflow has no trigger.config.secret."
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"payload\": \"from webhook\",\n  \"foo\": 1\n}"
            },
            "url": "{{baseUrl}}/webhook/{{workflowId}}",
            "description": "Enqueues a BullMQ job (`execute-workflow`). Response **202** JSON: `message`, `jobId` (queue id). Requires **published** workflow. Worker runs `executeWorkflow`; **Run.jobId** matches queue **jobId**."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}
